FYI: NTSC stands for:  (National Television Systems Committee). It is referring to the way that the picture is "scanned" onto your TV screen. The other main standard is PAL. 

PAL stand for (Phase Alternate Line) It is a little bit better as far as resolution but now, HI-DEF is pretty much the norm. and so much better then either of the fore mentioned formats, that it makes NTSC and PAL look like a joke.
